			<ns0:name>krasin@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/krasin@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
PNaCl is not fully ABI-compatible with NNaCl, so that it's not always possible to call a function from PNaCl executable to the native .so.

The known cases include small structure by value, unions, complex, _Bool, etc.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
PNaCl must be fully compatible with nacl-gcc. 

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
We need to have tests for such compatibility. There's native_client/tests/callingconv test that covers some of the cases, but it's hard to understand, hard to enhance and does not cover all known cases.

We need another, manual, more comprehensive test.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;

All known ABI-compatibility issues are covered by the test (with the known failures).
Adding a new case is easy.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
We'll be better understand where we are in PNaCl/NNaCl ABI compatibility.
